issue.title: esphome-dsckeybus keeps system busy while "toruble light" flashes makes complete alarm system unavailable
issue.body:
Hi,
first of all thanks for the grate work, it is awesome.
One issue I recognized that when there is a FLASHING! trouble light in the system (e.h.: both alarm and trouble are present, and alarm and trouble light flashes alternately) then esphome-dsckeybus keeps the system busy therefore not available.

Practical example:
- Alarm triggered by tamper
- System goes into alarm mode (siren is active)
- Then both "Alarm" and "Trouble" start flashing alternately.
- esphome-dsckeybus keeps system busy therefore user not even able to disable alarm from keypad (gets system busy message always)
- only solution is to disconnect esphome-dsckeybus and then system goes back to normal

My suspicion is that this function causes the issue:
`
#flag to have the esp check for trouble statuses for devices/zones when the trouble light goes on or off
#Note: It will prevent the physical panel from beeping to let you know as the check resets the beep.
#Sends *21 and *27 to the panel. Default: true

trouble_fetch: true
`
I believe the root cause is that due to both "alarm" and "trouble" present in the system, the "trouble" light not just goes ON, but flashing alternately with "alarm" with ~1sec period. Each and every time when "trouble" light goes on (w/ ~1sec period) esphome-dsckeybus reads troubles but because of the frequent period, keeps the bus busy therefore prevents everyone else on the bus to communicate (including keypads).

If the problem is really the one above, then one possible solution could be that it is limited that how often troubles are being read if trouble light is flashing. e.g.: if troubles has been read due to trouble light went ON then for a certain period of time (10sec? or parameter?) troubles will be not read even though trouble light went ON again.

As an intermittent solution I set "trouble_fetch: false" but would be good if I can keep this function running (e.g.: trigger automation as soon as any trouble appears not just reading with a certain period with (trouble_fetch_update_time")

My system:
- DSC PC1616
- 2x PK5507
- Signal PS128A-1 Siren
-  esphome-dsckeybus

issue.body:
In the URI-PackageURL tests (which use JSON definitions of PURL types for validation), I have a problem with Swift.

```
    # [base] invalid swift purl without version
    # pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- INPUT: pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- REGEXP: (?^:^pkg:(([/]{1,})?)([A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9\.\-]*)([/]{1,}).+)
-- S1: pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- S2: pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- S3: pkg swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- S4: swift github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- S5: github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
-- S6: github.com Alamofire
-- Loaded 'URI::PackageURL::Type::swift' class
-- Loaded 'swift-definition.json' type definition schema
-- Validation - Evaluate namespace_definition requirement rule -- is required

    #   Failed test 'DECODE pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire: invalid swift purl without version'
    #   at t/99-purl-tests.t line 120.
    #                   ''
    #     doesn't match '(?^i:(Invalid|Malformed) PURL)'
    # [base] invalid swift purl without version
    # pkg:swift/github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire
```

In the old PURL-TYPES, the version was required, but now it is not specified.

https://github.com/package-url/purl-spec/blob/a9ba953fc61b5db49b7a9c42373c6fad902ad2e7/PURL-TYPES.rst?plain=1#L602-L613

The tests for Swift require the version to be required (the previous error).

release.name: v0.2.0
release.body:
## What's Changed

Significant updates to repository automation, CI/CD workflows, and configuration files to modernize the project and streamline development processes (https://github.com/andreygrechin/webcolors/pull/21).

**CI/CD Workflow Modernization:**

* Added new GitHub Actions workflows for linting (`.github/workflows/lint.yml`), publishing container images (`.github/workflows/publish.yml`), dependency review, cache cleanup, author assignment, issue/MR closure, and secret scanning, replacing older workflows and enhancing automation and security. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-107e910e9f2ebfb9a741fa10b2aa7100cc1fc4f5f3aca2dfe78b905cbd73c0d2R1-R32) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-551d1fcf87f78cc3bc18a7b332a4dc5d8773a512062df881c5aba28a6f5c48d7R1-R66) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-9cbc51eceafcef442bca26f982efae9bc095dc325359595ef0ef69b4195f1222R1-R15) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-8945a3361778b570d0b11fc891f119ef85ed7959a3f49cac6c914a76626bc36eR1-R13) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-cf2fc1b2155cff28bfdb206f1d53b1da1a8a1d1c3f13f481992fba81865f558aR1-R15) [[6]](diffhunk://#diff-54a6de3722428e960ecf9e7c62854307a1298f0f2c64afce5e77602fb0ad430bR1-R14) [[7]](diffhunk://#diff-2aa7a05eafb406b4c582ed3bd35f2ef3a6fadeaad31372f62a79bd7610e1e453R1-R17)
* Removed legacy workflow files (`.github/workflows/lint.yaml`, `.github/workflows/publish.yaml`) to avoid confusion and ensure only updated workflows are used. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-4b122024a3a28ded65da76a2f1bface1f3a27328374438d1298d25585fe0603bL1-L30) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-e81e13daadd1745de51d8b8d85fce1fcd9be355732b64d60a6b56e18c28388caL1-L78)

**Dockerfile and Build Improvements:**

* Refactored the `Dockerfile` to use Python 3.13 and the `uv` package manager for faster, reproducible builds, multi-stage building, and unprivileged user execution for better security.

**Configuration and Repo Hygiene:**

* Expanded `.dockerignore` to exclude additional development and cache directories, improving build context and security.
* Removed `.gitmodules` and submodule references to simplify repository management.
* Updated `.editorconfig` by removing redundant Makefile rules for consistency.

**GitHub Metadata and Templates:**

* Updated `.github/dependabot.yaml` to reduce update frequency to semiannual and limit open PRs, adding `dependabot` labels for clarity.
* Removed issue templates and configuration file to streamline issue creation and reduce maintenance overhead. (`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml`)
* Replaced the Code of Conduct with a concise, plain-language version for greater accessibility and clarity. (`.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`)

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/andreygrechin/webcolors/compare/v0.1.21...v0.2.0
